    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-11T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-11T01:00:00-05:00" n="424"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9331/173: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-11T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 11, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 11—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Department’s 6, January 9, 5 p.m. Note to Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    bearing date January 13 has been mailed to Peck<note n="58" xml:id="d424fn58"
                        >Willys R. Peck, Counselor of Legation and Consul General at Nanking.</note>
                    today for delivery on the 13th. The second sentence of first paragraph was
                    drafted to read as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Under date of January 3, 1934, I informed Your Excellency that your note
                            under reference had been communicated to my Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
